#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:6
msgid "Areas"
msgstr "Vùng -- Areas"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:8
msgid "The application window is divided up into a number of rectangular areas. Areas reserve screen space for :doc:`/editors/index`, such as 3D Viewport, or an Outliner. Area boundary is indicated by rounded (beveled) corners."
msgstr "The application window is divided up into a number of rectangular areas. Areas reserve screen space for :doc:`/editors/index`, such as 3D Viewport, or an Outliner. Area boundary is indicated by rounded (beveled) corners."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:15
msgid "Area boundaries are indicated by rounded corners (yellow highlights)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:18
msgid "Resizing"
msgstr "Đổi Kích Thước -- Resizing"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:22
msgid "You can resize areas by dragging their borders with :kbd:`LMB`. Move your mouse cursor over the border between two areas, so that the cursor changes to a double-headed arrow, and then click and drag."
msgstr "You can resize areas by dragging their borders with :kbd:`LMB`. Move your mouse cursor over the border between two areas, so that the cursor changes to a double-headed arrow, and then click and drag."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:27
msgid "Splitting and Joining"
msgstr "Tách Phân và Hội Nhập-- Splitting and Joining"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:31
msgid "Splitting an area will create a new area, and joining of two areas will close one area. Placing mouse cursor in area corner will change cursor to a cross (+) to indicate that pressing down :kbd:`LMB` will activate splitting or joining command. Dragging from area corner inward will *split* the area. You define the split direction by dragging either horizontally or vertically."
msgstr "Splitting an area will create a new area, and joining of two areas will close one area. Placing mouse cursor in area corner will change cursor to a cross (+) to indicate that pressing down :kbd:`LMB` will activate splitting or joining command. Dragging from area corner inward will *split* the area. You define the split direction by dragging either horizontally or vertically."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:40
msgid "The Properties Editor is being joined to the Outliner."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:42
msgid "Dragging from area corner outward will *join* two areas. The area that will be closed gets a dark overlaid arrow. You can select which area will be closed by moving the mouse over areas. Release the :kbd:`LMB` to complete the join. If you press :kbd:`Esc` or :kbd:`RMB` before releasing the mouse, the operation will be aborted."
msgstr "Dragging from area corner outward will *join* two areas. The area that will be closed gets a dark overlaid arrow. You can select which area will be closed by moving the mouse over areas. Release the :kbd:`LMB` to complete the join. If you press :kbd:`Esc` or :kbd:`RMB` before releasing the mouse, the operation will be aborted."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:50
msgid "Areas to be joined must be the same size (width or height) in the direction you wish to join, otherwise nothing will happen. This is so that the combined area remains a rectangle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:56
msgid "Area Options"
msgstr "Tùy Chọn về Khu Vực -- Area Options"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:58
msgid ":kbd:`RMB` on the border opens the *Area Options*."
msgstr ":kbd:`RMB` on the border opens the *Area Options*."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:61
msgid "Split Area"
msgstr "Tách phân Khu Vực -- Split Area"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:61
msgid "Shows an indicator line that lets you select the area and position where to split. :kbd:`Tab` switches between vertical/horizontal."
msgstr "Shows an indicator line that lets you select the area and position where to split. :kbd:`Tab` switches between vertical/horizontal."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:65
msgid "Join Areas"
msgstr "Hội Nhập các Vùng-- Join Areas"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:64
msgid "Shows the join direction overlay."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:68
msgid "Swapping Contents"
msgstr "Tráo Đổi Nội Dung -- Swapping Contents"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:70
msgid "You can swap the contents between two areas with :kbd:`Ctrl-LMB` on one of the corners of the initial area, dragging towards the target area, and releasing the mouse there. The two areas do not need to be side-by-side, though they must be inside the same window."
msgstr "You can swap the contents between two areas with :kbd:`Ctrl-LMB` on one of the corners of the initial area, dragging towards the target area, and releasing the mouse there. The two areas do not need to be side-by-side, though they must be inside the same window."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:79
msgid "Duplicate Area into new Window"
msgstr "Sao Chép Vùng vào Cửa Sổ Mới-- Duplicate Area into new Window"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:81
#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:101
#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:124
msgid "Reference"
msgstr "Tham Chiếu -- Reference"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst
msgid "Menu"
