msgstr ":menuselection:`View --> Duplicate Area into new Window`"

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:86
msgid "A new floating window containing an area can be created from :menuselection:`View --> Duplicate Area into new Window`."
msgstr "A new floating window containing an area can be created from :menuselection:`View --> Duplicate Area into new Window`."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:89
msgid "The new window is a fully functional window, which is part of the same instance of Blender. This can be useful, e.g. if you have multiple monitors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:92
msgid "You can also create a new window from an existing area by :kbd:`Shift-LMB` on the area corner, then drag outward slightly."
msgstr "You can also create a new window from an existing area by :kbd:`Shift-LMB` on the area corner, then drag outward slightly."

#: ../../manual/interface/window_system/areas.rst:95
msgid "The window can be closed with the OS *Close Window* button."
